      transliteration: 'ātmaupamyena sarvatra samaṁ paśyati yo \'rjuna\nsukhaṁ vā yadi vā duḥkhaṁ sa yogī paramo mataḥ',
      translation: 'One who sees the equality of all beings through likeness with the self — whether in joy or in sorrow — that yogi is considered the highest, O Arjuna.',
